info.title: Best Execution Analytics for Smarter Trading (BEAST) API
info.description: Enables clients to programmatically access the underlying data which powers the BEAST Liquidity Analytics (LA) and Transaction Cost Analysis (TCA) applications.

parameters.name: securityId
parameters.description: ISIN for European or India securities, otherwise TICKER. Works together with country and currency parameters.

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: The two character ISO country code of the trading region, like US. EMEA is used for the European trading region

parameters.name: orderVolume
parameters.description: Order Volume in scientific notation or float format. Example: 1000 or 1.234567e4.

parameters.name: strategy
parameters.description: Specify the strategy, choices are: Optimal, VWAP, TWAP, Custom

parameters.name: riskAversion
parameters.description: Input risk tolerance from passive to very aggressive

parameters.name: startTime
parameters.description: Start Time in the format HH:MM

parameters.name: endTime
parameters.description: End Time in the format HH:MM

parameters.name: isMomentum
parameters.description: Flag to apply stock momentum. Specify true to include momentum

parameters.name: side
parameters.description: Indicate whether a buyer or seller. Only applies when isMomentum is true. Example: Buy or Sell

parameters.name: peer
parameters.description: Flag to apply peer calibration. Specify true to include peer calibration

parameters.name: rearLoadHalfLife
parameters.description: Delays orders towards end of the trading day

parameters.name: binsData
parameters.description: Flag to apply BinsData. Specify true to include BinsData

parameters.description: The winsorization deviation - standard deviation to define orders as outlier

get.description: Get Orders by specific field values.

parameters.name: securityId
parameters.description: ISIN for European or India securities, otherwise TICKER. Works together with country and currency parameters.

parameters.name: trader
parameters.description: Optionally specify a trader to filter by, Example : Ryan

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: The two character ISO country code of the trading region, like US. EMEA is used for the European trading region

parameters.name: strategy
parameters.description: Specify the strategy, choices are: Optimal, VWAP, TWAP, Custom

parameters.name: orderFields
parameters.description: Specify order fields to select. The OrderId, Country, MasterOrderId, MessageType and ParentId fields are default fields and must be included if none are specified.

parameters.name: hierarchical
parameters.description: Return order records in hierarchical format or as flat records

parameters.name: messageType
parameters.description: Return parent or child order records by messageType. Only apply when hierarchical is false

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Maximum number of records to return per page. Default with max value 50000

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Starting position (offset) for paginated records. Specifies current page to return results. Default value 1
